SharePoint will be upgraded from SharePoint 2019 to SharePoint Subscription Edition over the weekend.
The existing SharePoint URL will remain the same, and we do not expect any major changes for users once the upgrade is complete.
SharePoint may be unavailable or intermittently available during the weekend while the cutover work is completed.
SharePoint is expected to be available again by Monday morning.
SharePoint Online will remain available during the weekend. However, links from the on-premise SharePoint portal to SharePoint Online sites may not be available while the portal itself is down.
On Monday morning, users should close and reopen their browser, or restart their PC, before accessing SharePoint. This will help clear any old sessions and allow a clean login.
If users experience issues on Monday, they should first try closing all browser windows and reopening SharePoint.
If the issue continues, users should try a hard refresh of the page before logging a support ticket.
Any issues that remain after restarting the browser or PC should be logged through the normal support process.
